##A special report on all living beings in "besieged city" in Hubei Province

Micro Signal Xincaijing

Function introduction, the recorder of new business, the promoter of New Economy.

Story Teller
Editor / Sze Ka

Since January 23,10:00 in Wuhan, in order to further prevent the spread of the epidemic, Wuhan and other surrounding cities have also made the city closure measures. As if overnight, the entire province of Hubei completely into a closed state.

Hubei has a permanent population of 59.17 million, according to National Bureau of Statistics of the People's Republic of China statistics in 2018. In addition to being a populous province, Hubei also exports a large number of excellent laborers to other parts of the country every year. For those who work outside the city, the day after the Spring Festival is supposed to be a return trip, but because of the disaster, everyone has to stay in their cities.

Despite their plight, they are fighting the epidemic in their own way... And among them, some people rush to the front, some people call off the wedding, some people take the initiative to self-isolation... .

Here are four ordinary people working in Hubei Province who are feeling and thinking about the outbreak, according to a report by Zinccaijing.

"Even if a person in Wuhan Chinese New Year, I also feel very secure. "
DICTATION: L

HOMETOWN: Wuhan, Hubei Province
Working Place: Wuhan
Occupation: stylist
ORAL DATE: January 29

I was born and raised in Wuhan. I was a witness to the whole outbreak and was involved in it. But, unlike the reports on the Internet, people in Wuhan are quite scared and anxious. On the contrary, I feel that Wuhan is the safest place.

On January 20, after we all had dinner together, my parents went to Caidian District because of something, but it turned out to be our family's lunar New Year dinner. It was announced in the early morning of the 23rd that the city would be closed at 10 a.m, my parents planned to come back overnight, but I told them to stay in Caidian District because the situation in Wuhan was serious and it wasn't safe to come back in the middle of the night. Before my parents left, I had a lot of food and drink in the fridge, which became all the food I needed to stay home alone.

I haven't been out of the House since the 23rd and am completely cut off from the rest of the world except for the hard news, Video Games, TV and sleep. And when I wake up in the morning, I can basically receive a lot of friends'greetings, ask me what I still lack, Wuhan is not very serious now, what to do at home and so on.

For these, I will tell them I am very good, not short of anything, at the same time also told them that Wuhan is not as terrible as they imagined.

Sometimes it is really a panic, want to go out, I will take the news and reports to remind myself never to go out, at home is the safest.

Then, one day, the water in my home suddenly ran out. I was really thirsty. I wanted to go to the supermarket. However, when I thought about the news report that the supermarkets were all closed, I decided to try my luck. Therefore, when I went out, it's pretty heavily armed: masks, hats, gloves. Downstairs, found that the first floor of the store is still open, I rushed to the recent lack of things all one-time procurement finished, ready to go out again.

After this experience, I think shopping sometimes do not have to go to the big supermarket, people are also susceptible to infection, critical period, at home in the door of the small supermarket shopping is relatively convenient and safe.

In fact, Wuhan City, everyone's mentality is still pretty good, and not much panic, like I live in this community also held a collective singing activities. I also participated in this event, but I was not prepared to participate in the previous, it was completely the atmosphere of the time, really moved, in retrospect still tears.

Before the 27th, someone had announced in various groups that everyone would sing together. By about 7:30 that evening, there were many people in my neighborhood lighting up with their mobile phones and flashlights. At first, not many people, later, more and more people filled the whole neighborhood with a different atmosphere. It was completely different from the dead silence of the previous few days. Some people were shouting for gas in Wuhan, some were shouting and singing, and some were quarrelling. It was about 8 o'clock, then someone started shouting "one, two, three" and started to sing, and then everyone started to sing.

Singing scene in the interviewee's circle of friends

I was going to stand in the window to watch, but that scene is hard to say you do not go into it, really touched, can not help but sing along, I also shot with a cell phone. I remember singing with a mask on because there were reports on the Internet that droplets could also spread the virus.

In fact, I think Wuhan is the Safest City in Hubei compared to other cities. After all, good medical conditions and resources are here, and people's awareness of prevention has been gradually raised. It's really safe to stay at home. Some of my colleagues are from Ensch (another city in Hubei) . They heard that they came back from Wuhan. Some people scolded them. In fact, they did a lot of protection and inspection before going back, and voluntarily quarantined at home, it's not worth it to think about.

"I had a CT scan so I wouldn't infect my family. "
ORAL: Sheep, sheep, sheep, sheep, sheep

HOMETOWN: Hubei Public Security
Occupation: Tutor for postgraduate entrance examination
Working Place: Wuhan
ORAL PRESENTATION: January 30

I actually began to pay attention to this matter very early, because usually I myself attach importance to medical knowledge. When I returned to my hometown on the 21st, I found that my body temperature was a little high. I was afraid that I was infected with Wuhan Pneumonia, because I do take the subway every day will pass through the gold and silver lake this disaster area, so I went to the hospital to take a CT examination, fortunately, false alarm.

I remember in late December, someone on my wechat group sent in an internal document from a hospital (it was reported on the Internet later) . After seeing the document, my gut feeling was that the virus wasn't as simple as it was usually reported, and since then, I've been wearing a mask on the subway every day.

What impressed me most was December 31, after work that day, the bus was particularly congested, usually 20 minutes to get there, that day took more than an hour, get off the train to the subway is the same, wait for several times to be crowded. I was sensitive and resistant, because it was the last day of December, and a lot of people were going downtown for New Year's Eve, but I saw that almost no one was wearing a mask.

Respondents'circle of friends for the day

At that time, few people took the virus seriously. People really began to pay attention to it around January 19, because online public opinion began to ferment, there were whispers that the information was coming from inside the hospital.

I was going to go home on January 23rd because my own tutorial class was supposed to end on the 21st. But since the 19th, there was more and more news on the Internet. I felt the situation was more serious than I thought. Some students began to wear masks in class that day. So I immediately changed my train ticket and went home early on the 21st night.

When I went to work on the 21st, I found that most of the people in the subway already wore masks, and very few of them didn't, so I wore double masks just to be safe. That day, in addition to class, other time in the online news and the progress of the disease, I even prepared to go directly to the train station after class, because the only way home is through the gold and silver lake this disaster area. But since I hadn't packed anything, I hurried back to my place.

Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital (net map, invasion and deletion)

The first thing I did when I got back to my apartment was to take my temperature, because I usually pay more attention to these things. We always have a thermometer at home. After taking the temperature, I found it was 37.4 °C, slightly above normal body temperature. I was afraid that I would be quarantined at the railway station, because some colleagues who went home that morning said that the station had staff in the temperature test.

I came to the train station with my heart in my hands, but there was no staff member to take my temperature. I don't know if there was no equipment or what the reason was. I wasn't checked by the police anyway, but I saw that no staff member in the train station, or were all the passengers wearing masks, and they were both happy and scared.

When I got home, I started obsessively scrolling through the news, getting a tug on my heart with every new statistic, every infection I reported, and wondering if I was infected, too.

The next day I couldn't sit still. I sent my mother to buy a thermometer and found it was between 36.4 °C and 37 °C. Although it was a normal temperature, some people had reported no symptoms of fever, but it turned out that they still had a lung infection, and My mother is not well, the resistance is poor, I really fear that if I infected, the infection to the family.

On the second day of my return, the 23rd, I decided to go to our city hospital fully armed for further examination. I had all my daily necessities ready, ready to carry, and was ready to be quarantined.

Photos of interviewees going out

When I arrived at the hospital, I found that many people had just returned from Wuhan. Some had a low-grade fever, some felt uncomfortable. In short, they all suspected that they had contracted a new type of pneumonia and came to the hospital for a confirmation check. After I explained the situation to the doctor, the doctor said they can only do tests, but whether the test is confirmed, can only go to Wuhan.

Because I was in a hurry at the time, and I said, let's check first, and I deliberately hung up on the emergency room, hoping to get the results soon, I did two tests: Blood draw and CT, I remember when I went to the CT, I looked at the CT bed, in front of several people are using the same one-time Blue Shield, I asked the doctor why not change, the doctor said, "long out of stock, you do not know? ". It can be seen that the small cities under Hubei were also extremely short of medical materials at that time.

When I got the results of my examination, the doctor said that my physical condition was quite normal. He told me to go home and check my temperature the next day. Sure enough, the next day, I had a check, 36.4 °C. However, I still didn't take it lightly for a week, he doesn't leave his room or his living room.

Survey report of interviewees

The community recently every day there are trumpets in the promotion of new pneumonia protection and other knowledge, my mother also took the initiative to report my situation to the community staff, now also slowly calm down, and enjoy the peace and happiness with their families.

"The wedding is delayed, but love is not. "
DICTATION: Mike
HOMETOWN: Hubei Xiantao
Place of Work: Xuzhou
Occupation: Construction Engineer of a group
ORAL PRESENTATION: January 30

We were originally scheduled to get married on the sixth day of the first lunar month (January 30) , but due to the epidemic, the wedding was postponed. The specific date has not been decided yet. I think the earliest we can do is "May 1" , right? If we don't do it soon, it will be almost "11" , usually we are too busy with work, wedding big and small things are quite a lot, so after the estimated or will choose a long vacation.

She and I began to fall in love in June of 17, is in the entrance examination of the postgraduate know, she is my elder sister, a year older than me. Because of the work, we are basically a long distance, there are disputes in the middle, but the last two people still adhere to. Because of the age is not small, coupled with the urging of the family, we met in October 19 both parents set a time: 2020 Lunar New Year's Day six.

So I went home early for Chinese New Year. On January 18th, I took a bullet train from Xuzhou to my hometown. In the middle of the Hankou Railway Station, yes, there was the south China seafood market, and there were almost no masks at the train station. Although know that this matter, but still relatively calm, transfer add waiting for the train, in the railway station for about two hours.

Hankou Railway Station

Looking back on it now, I can't help but be afraid.

Back home, around the 20th, reports of the epidemic began to be frequent, and even every hour there will be a push of progress, I began to be alert, feeling that this is not an ordinary disease, began to refresh the news frequently, in particular, when it was reported that someone had contracted the infection after only a short stay in Wuhan, I began to subconsciously isolate myself, basically staying at home and regretting why I had to transfer from the Hankou station.

On the 21st, after I saw that the medical staff was infected and confirmed that it could be passed on from one person to another, I began to think about whether to cancel the wedding and discussed it with my family. At first, they were not very supportive of the postponement. After all, the awareness of my parents'generation is not as high as ours, until they saw it on TV themselves, and there was some publicity in town, and they took it.

Starting from the 22nd, I began to inform friends and relatives, especially the teachers and classmates from other places, to prepare for the refund and cancellation of the trip in advance. Fortunately, everyone quite understand, also support my decision, this point, let me some peace of mind and touched.

Screenshots of wedding cancellations provided by interviewees

At the same time, I also discussed with my in-laws whether their side should cancel together. Although we are both in Hubei Province, but not in the same city, the original plan was that the fifth day would be the official date of their family. I married her from her family and took her to our hotel, the sixth day is the official date of our family, I took her from the hotel to my home.

At first, the in-laws did not agree, because all the relatives and friends had been informed, and the time was tight. They still planned to go ahead as originally planned. Unexpectedly, a few days later, their city was closed, too, so on the 23rd, it was all set, both parties postponed, and the wedding was officially canceled.

I actually appreciate my wife's decision to postpone the wedding, she has always supported me, and now I'm stuck at home, I do nothing but chat with her on Wechat all day long to relieve my boredom. According to the current situation, i don't think we're GONNA see each other for at least another month.

"with a confirmed case in the same department, I go home and stay away from my family. "
DICTATION: Lu Lu
HOMETOWN: Jingzhou, Hubei
Place of Work: Jingzhou
Occupation: Fever nurse
ORAL DATE: January 29

I am a fever department nurse, January 24 morning after the end of rotation, New Year's Eve 30 at home and family had dinner, the first morning of the first day immediately back to the hospital, the fourth round of the first day after the end of the post, back home to do self-isolation, the hospital situation is too complicated, i'm afraid to pass it on to my family.

Since about January 20, our department has been completely on the rampage, full of patients, quarantined patients and busy medical staff, and I as a "new person" working for less than two years, it feels like the last 10 days have been half a century.

I received the notice from January 20 that all staff must be on duty. It is compulsory to be on duty. It is not like the online upload that there are lots drawn, party members and single students first, etc. . Perhaps our small place really is not so full of medical and nursing staff.

I remember when I arrived at the post, we more or less some resistance and dissatisfaction, because we such a career, usually do not have much time to rest, this time even the Spring Festival are directly. Since arriving at the Post, the director has been emphasizing the seriousness and highly infectious nature of pneumonia in Wuhan. Let us pay special attention to those patients who have fever and cough weakness. At the same time, let us do our best to protect ourselves and must wear masks, keep your distance from the seriously ill.

Our protective equipment at that time was very simple, that is the common mask, head cover, gloves, foot cover, but also very scarce, there is no so-called protective clothing and goggles, these are around the 28th, is also very scarce.

Medical Staff (net map, invasion and deletion)

Because I am a nurse, most of the day-to-day work is still to take temperature, hang water, do case records, according to the attending doctor's medical records do patient care. Since the 21st, there has been a marked increase in the number of patients coming to the hospital. Many of them are returning home from Wuhan. They think their condition is similar to the Wuhan Virus reported in the news, so they want to be tested. To tell the truth, for such patients, our department is quite disgusted, originally we have been very busy, all kinds of materials are lacking, now it is a nuisance, in my opinion at that time the hospital is not safer than their own home.

January 24th is New Year's Eve. The department head said that some of our younger and weaker colleagues should go home early, at least for a New Year's Eve dinner with their families. We initially disagreed, but later we couldn't stand her advice and did have a little desire to go back and have a look, since the 20th, my clothes have been a little stinky.

So we packed up at noon on the 23rd and went home. Before going home, I asked my parents to prepare a lot of disinfectant in advance. Before entering the House, I sprayed 3 times all over my body before entering the house. After dinner on New Year's Eve, my mother kept asking me if I was tired and dangerous, actually at that time our section already had the confirmed case, I did not dare to say more, feared that they worried.

That night, I didn't sleep soundly either. I kept thinking of my colleagues who were still in the hospital. The next morning, after a simple New Year's visit with my parents, I was going to start. At that time, the city buses had stopped running. My father drove me to the hospital. After I arrived at the hospital, i didn't dare let him stay another second. I got out of the car and turned him around.

Jingzhou doctors set up isolation observation point of traditional Chinese medicine

If years ago was the state of preparation, years later is the real battlefield, the first phase of the incubation period is coming, will usher in a new outbreak. The number of confirmed cases changed every day, and the number of suspected cases could not be counted. At that time, we could only take care of the most serious cases. After putting on the protective clothing, we could not take it off for at least half a day. First, it was a waste of time to put it on and take it off. Second, this suit was taken off, we may not have the next suit to wear, and we rarely drink water in order to reduce our bathroom breaks. And in this process, almost no time to see the phone, sometimes only in the meal that will brush down, during my parents sent me a lot of information, are just look, also no time back.

As for the information on the Internet, our medical staff is also numb, may be in the midst of it, but relatively calm bar. See oneself check the case has been diagnosed, at first more surprised and panic, then slowly calm down, there is time to feel oneself and the virus into one, but will deliberately and people around to keep away.

After the fourth round of the seventh lunar month, I myself walked back. Originally, my home and the hospital were fairly close. However, this time, I did not enter the gate of the new house. I went directly to the old house. My parents were afraid that I would suffer. They said they were not afraid of infection, but I thought it would make me feel better, because many of my colleagues go home, isolated from each other, and some don't even want to go home.

(the paramedic remained at his post as of this writing.)

Looking back on it now, I can't help but be afraid.

On the 21st, after I saw that the medical staff was infected and confirmed that it could be passed on from one person to another, I began to think about whether to cancel the wedding and discussed it with my family. At first, they were not very supportive of the postponement. After all, the awareness of my parents'generation is not as high as ours, until they saw it on TV themselves, and there was some publicity in town, and they took it.

Starting from the 22nd, I began to inform friends and relatives, especially the teachers and classmates from other places, to prepare for the refund and cancellation of the trip in advance. Fortunately, everyone quite understand, also support my decision, this point, let me some peace of mind and touched.

Screenshots of wedding cancellations provided by interviewees

At the same time, I also discussed with my in-laws whether their side should cancel together. Although we are both in Hubei Province, but not in the same city, the original plan was that the fifth day would be the official date of their family. I married her from her family and took her to our hotel, the sixth day is the official date of our family, I took her from the hotel to my home.

At first, the in-laws did not agree, because all the relatives and friends had been informed, and the time was tight. They still planned to go ahead as originally planned. Unexpectedly, a few days later, their city was closed, too, so on the 23rd, it was all set, both parties postponed, and the wedding was officially canceled.

I actually appreciate my wife's decision to postpone the wedding, she has always supported me, and now I'm stuck at home, I do nothing but chat with her on Wechat all day long to relieve my boredom. According to the current situation, i don't think we're GONNA see each other for at least another month.

"with a confirmed case in the same department, I go home and stay away from my family. "

DICTATION: Lu Lu
HOMETOWN: Jingzhou, Hubei
Place of Work: Jingzhou
Occupation: Fever nurse
ORAL DATE: January 29

DICTATION: Lu Lu

HOMETOWN: Jingzhou, Hubei

Place of Work: Jingzhou

Occupation: Fever nurse

I am a fever department nurse, January 24 morning after the end of rotation, New Year's Eve 30 at home and family had dinner, the first morning of the first day immediately back to the hospital, the fourth round of the first day after the end of the post, back home to do self-isolation, the hospital situation is too complicated, i'm afraid to pass it on to my family.

Since about January 20, our department has been completely on the rampage, full of patients, quarantined patients and busy medical staff, and I as a "new person" working for less than two years, it feels like the last 10 days have been half a century.

I received the notice from January 20 that all staff must be on duty. It is compulsory to be on duty. It is not like the online upload that there are lots drawn, party members and single students first, etc. . Perhaps our small place really is not so full of medical and nursing staff.

I remember when I arrived at the post, we more or less some resistance and dissatisfaction, because we such a career, usually do not have much time to rest, this time even the Spring Festival are directly. Since arriving at the Post, the director has been emphasizing the seriousness and highly infectious nature of pneumonia in Wuhan. Let us pay special attention to those patients who have fever and cough weakness. At the same time, let us do our best to protect ourselves and must wear masks, keep your distance from the seriously ill.

Our protective equipment at that time was very simple, that is the common mask, head cover, gloves, foot cover, but also very scarce, there is no so-called protective clothing and goggles, these are around the 28th, is also very scarce.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medical Staff (net map, invasion and deletion)

Because I am a nurse, most of the day-to-day work is still to take temperature, hang water, do case records, according to the attending doctor's medical records do patient care. Since the 21st, there has been a marked increase in the number of patients coming to the hospital. Many of them are returning home from Wuhan. They think their condition is similar to the Wuhan Virus reported in the news, so they want to be tested. To tell the truth, for such patients, our department is quite disgusted, originally we have been very busy, all kinds of materials are lacking, now it is a nuisance, in my opinion at that time the hospital is not safer than their own home.

January 24th is New Year's Eve. The department head said that some of our younger and weaker colleagues should go home early, at least for a New Year's Eve dinner with their families. We initially disagreed, but later we couldn't stand her advice and did have a little desire to go back and have a look, since the 20th, my clothes have been a little stinky.

So we packed up at noon on the 23rd and went home. Before going home, I asked my parents to prepare a lot of disinfectant in advance. Before entering the House, I sprayed 3 times all over my body before entering the house. After dinner on New Year's Eve, my mother kept asking me if I was tired and dangerous, actually at that time our section already had the confirmed case, I did not dare to say more, feared that they worried.

That night, I didn't sleep soundly either. I kept thinking of my colleagues who were still in the hospital. The next morning, after a simple New Year's visit with my parents, I was going to start. At that time, the city buses had stopped running. My father drove me to the hospital. After I arrived at the hospital, i didn't dare let him stay another second. I got out of the car and turned him around.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jingzhou doctors set up isolation observation point of traditional Chinese medicine

If years ago was the state of preparation, years later is the real battlefield, the first phase of the incubation period is coming, will usher in a new outbreak. The number of confirmed cases changed every day, and the number of suspected cases could not be counted. At that time, we could only take care of the most serious cases. After putting on the protective clothing, we could not take it off for at least half a day. First, it was a waste of time to put it on and take it off. Second, this suit was taken off, we may not have the next suit to wear, and we rarely drink water in order to reduce our bathroom breaks. And in this process, almost no time to see the phone, sometimes only in the meal that will brush down, during my parents sent me a lot of information, are just look, also no time back.

As for the information on the Internet, our medical staff is also numb, may be in the midst of it, but relatively calm bar. See oneself check the case has been diagnosed, at first more surprised and panic, then slowly calm down, there is time to feel oneself and the virus into one, but will deliberately and people around to keep away.

After the fourth round of the seventh lunar month, I myself walked back. Originally, my home and the hospital were fairly close. However, this time, I did not enter the gate of the new house. I went directly to the old house. My parents were afraid that I would suffer. They said they were not afraid of infection, but I thought it would make me feel better, because many of my colleagues go home, isolated from each other, and some don't even want to go home.

(the paramedic remained at his post as of this writing.)
